Former team leader sentenced 10-1/2 years for bribery
2012-06-13 02:33:51 GMT
DANDONG, Liaoning Province, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Former Chinese national soccer team leader Wei Shaohui received a 10-1/2-year jail term and was fined 200,000 yuan (31,400 US dollars) for taking bribes.Minutes earlier, the ex-soccer chief Nan Yong received the same jail sentence.
